# Expenso environment overrides.
#
# Copy this file to ".env" (no extension) in the project root and edit as
# needed. The real ".env" is gitignored — you can safely put machine-
# specific paths in it. Lines starting with "#" are comments.
#
# All values are optional; comment a line out (or delete it) to use the
# default shown.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Where Expenso stores its CSV "database".
#
# CSV files in this folder are append-only at the file level: rows can be
# created / read / updated / row-deleted by the app, but the files themselves
# are never removed. Point this at an external drive / synced folder to keep
# your data outside the project tree.
#
# - Absolute paths are used as-is (Windows: D:/Backups/Expenso ;
#   POSIX: /Users/you/Documents/Expenso).
# - Relative paths are resolved against the project root.
# - "~" is expanded to your home directory.
#
# Default: ./data  (inside the project, gitignored)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# EXPENSO_DATA_DIR=D:/Backups/Expenso
# EXPENSO_DATA_DIR=~/Documents/Expenso

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Source workbook for the first-run seed and the top-bar "Re-import" button.
# Default: ~/Desktop/Expense_Tracker_FY2026-27.xlsx
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# EXPENSO_SOURCE_XLSX=~/Desktop/Expense_Tracker_FY2026-27.xlsx

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uvicorn bind address.
# Default: 127.0.0.1:8000  (localhost only)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# EXPENSO_HOST=127.0.0.1
# EXPENSO_PORT=8000